@startuml ambient_mode_to_bcm_cabin_light_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Ambient Mode To BCM Cabin Light Signal Flow\n(ambient mode -> BCM light publish)

participant "Ambient command /\nbody context" as AmbientCtx #F4F7FB
participant "BCM\nbody/light owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "Body light bus" as LightBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / ambient users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Light Inputs ==

AmbientCtx -> BCM : Cmd::ambientModeCmd / Body::ambientMode\ndriveState / scenario manual mode
BCM -> BCM : ambientMode = manual ? Cmd::ambientModeCmd : Body::ambientMode
BCM -> BCM : CabinLightMode = ambientMode & 0x7
BCM -> BCM : DomeLightLevel = (ambientMode > 0) ? 20 : 4
note right of BCM
Representative gating inputs
- Cmd::ambientModeCmd
- Body::ambientMode
- manualMode / driveState
end note

== Light Publish ==

BCM -> LightBus : frmLightStateMsg\nCabinLightMode / DomeLightLevel
note right of BCM
Representative outputs
- CabinLightMode
- DomeLightLevel
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

LightBus -> Obs : cabin-light readback /\nambient consumers

note over AmbientCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Ambient mode reaches BCM from manual or body-owned state
2. BCM translates ambient mode into cabin light state
3. BCM publishes cabin light mode and dome light level
4. Observers expose the effective body-light ambient posture
end note

@enduml
